  "status": "answered",
  "synthesis": {
    "answer": "`gobby-cli` does hybrid search by collecting ranked results from multiple sources, then fusing them with reciprocal rank fusion. The search command combines exact matching, BM25 full-text, and Qdrant semantic embeddings via RRF [crates/gcode/src/commands/search.rs:13-21]. The RRF wrapper forwards each named source’s ranked ID list to `gobby_core::search::rrf_merge` and converts the fused output into `(symbol_id, combined_score, source_names)` [crates/gcode/src/search/rrf.rs:7, crates/gcode/src/search/rrf.rs:15-20]. Evidence also shows that duplicate IDs accumulate score across sources and that source-name ordering is deterministic [crates/gcode/src/search/rrf.rs:27-34, crates/gcode/src/search/rrf.rs:37-49].",
